## Taxonomy field

This field type is used to display taxonomy terms for selection during submission. It can be single select or multi select, and has two display modes: Popup and Inline.

## General options

- Field name
- Field key
- Placeholder
- Description
- Is Required
- CSS Classes
- Default value

## Specific options

- **Choose taxonomy:** Lets you choose an existing taxonomy or create a new one
- **Display as:**Select between Popup and Inline display modes
- **Allow selection of multiple terms:**If enabled, user can pick multiple terms during submission
- **When editing posts through the WordPress backend, edit this field using**:Choose whether to display the taxonomy using WordPress native metabox or Voxel UI when creating posts in back-end.

Note: To display the native metabox on the block editor, you must also set Show this taxonomy in REST API to Yes in the taxonomy settings.
